1
00:00:01,140 --> 00:00:03,640
(Episode 67)

2
00:00:06,180 --> 00:00:09,280
What are you doing, Seo Rin?
Go on, play something for us.

3
00:00:12,820 --> 00:00:15,420
Prove to me that you're not Oh Jang Mi.

4
00:00:20,060 --> 00:00:21,060
Mrs. Yang?

5
00:00:22,530 --> 00:00:23,630
Yes, ma'am.

6
00:00:23,930 --> 00:00:26,000
Go get Seo Rin's violin.

7
00:00:30,500 --> 00:00:33,140
It needs tuning anyway, so I'll get it.

8
00:00:39,940 --> 00:00:43,210
I was so eager for you to hear
Seo Rin play.

9
00:00:43,780 --> 00:00:47,150
I invested so much in her lessons
when she was growing up.

10
00:00:47,920 --> 00:00:50,590
I'm sure you'll be smitten
when you hear her.

11
00:00:52,890 --> 00:00:55,030
Shall we have a toast in the meantime?

12
00:00:55,760 --> 00:00:56,760
Sure.

13
00:01:05,000 --> 00:01:09,240
Come on, have a seat.
You're not a stranger here.

14
00:01:11,840 --> 00:01:14,310
Team Leader Jin,
it's good to see you here.

15
00:01:14,850 --> 00:01:16,980
I hope I'm not intruding, coming so late.

16
00:01:17,450 --> 00:01:19,220
Professor, have you been well?

17
00:01:19,220 --> 00:01:21,590
Yes, of course, I've been doing great.

18
00:01:23,560 --> 00:01:24,960
Jin Hong Ju, what brings you here?

19
00:01:25,420 --> 00:01:27,830
It's rather rude to show up
at someone else's house this late,

20
00:01:28,260 --> 00:01:30,200
even if my mom was the one
who invited you.

21
00:01:30,460 --> 00:01:34,400
Baek Ho, that's no way to talk to a guest.

22
00:01:34,530 --> 00:01:38,240
Hong Ju didn't want to come.
I had to practically drag her here.

23
00:01:38,340 --> 00:01:41,710
Too bad. You should've tried harder
to say no.

24
00:01:42,270 --> 00:01:44,780
Oh, my. I'm sorry.

25
00:01:44,780 --> 00:01:46,440
You don't need to be sorry.

26
00:01:47,210 --> 00:01:49,850
Kang Baek Ho! Where are your manners?

27
00:01:51,280 --> 00:01:52,680
No, it's okay, ma'am.

28
00:01:53,020 --> 00:01:54,650
Baek Ho didn't do anything wrong.

29
00:01:55,090 --> 00:01:56,390
I wasn't being considerate.

30
00:01:56,860 --> 00:01:59,960
I didn't come here to make you
uncomfortable, Baek Ho.

31
00:02:01,660 --> 00:02:04,100
I should be on my way, ma'am.

32
00:02:05,300 --> 00:02:07,100
How could he treat someone
as sweet as you this way?

33
00:02:11,140 --> 00:02:14,770
Baek Ho, would you mind
taking me home instead?

34
00:02:15,810 --> 00:02:17,910
I didn't bring my car today.

35
00:02:18,310 --> 00:02:22,010
That sounds like a great idea.
Baek Ho, take her home.

36
00:02:30,920 --> 00:02:32,390
Do you mind if I take your arm?

37
00:02:33,390 --> 00:02:35,060
Why don't you just watch your step?

38
00:02:39,400 --> 00:02:43,130
It's so nice to be out here
alone with you.

39
00:02:49,970 --> 00:02:53,410
At my house, it's always so tense
with Director Ma and CEO Chae around.

40
00:02:54,250 --> 00:02:57,180
It's been a while
since I've gotten to just relax like this.

41
00:02:59,180 --> 00:03:00,790
Even though it was a short visit,

42
00:03:01,050 --> 00:03:03,790
it seems like your family
has such a warm home.

43
00:03:04,220 --> 00:03:06,560
Why are things so bad
at Chairman Ma's house?

44
00:03:06,720 --> 00:03:08,930
It's always like that.

45
00:03:09,690 --> 00:03:12,930
My mother remarried the Chairman.

46
00:03:13,930 --> 00:03:15,600
You get the picture, right?

47
00:03:18,300 --> 00:03:21,070
Everyone thought Director Ma
would inherit Dream Group.

48
00:03:21,810 --> 00:03:22,870
But a daughter is closer...

49
00:03:23,470 --> 00:03:24,810
than a granddaughter.

50
00:03:25,510 --> 00:03:29,050
Even though we're not blood-related,
based on my abilities and everything else,

51
00:03:29,410 --> 00:03:31,180
it looks like I'm the one
who will inherit Dream Group.

52
00:03:31,520 --> 00:03:33,020
So naturally, things are tense.

53
00:03:34,790 --> 00:03:35,790
Really?

54
00:03:47,800 --> 00:03:50,770
What's taking her so long?
She just went to get her violin.

55
00:03:53,710 --> 00:03:57,140
Seo Rin, you've loved the violin
ever since you were a little girl.

56
00:03:57,540 --> 00:04:01,050
Your body will remember
even if your mind doesn't.

57
00:04:01,480 --> 00:04:02,710
It's like riding a bike.

58
00:04:02,950 --> 00:04:06,050
But I'm nervous about playing
in front of Kang Jun Ho.

59
00:04:07,020 --> 00:04:10,250
Besides, I haven't played violin
in so long that my fingers are all stiff.

60
00:04:10,520 --> 00:04:13,560
It feels awkward when you haven't ridden
your bike in a while, right?

61
00:04:13,660 --> 00:04:15,560
You don't have to play
if you don't feel up to it.

62
00:04:15,630 --> 00:04:18,600
What are you talking about?
Of course you have to hear her play.

63
00:04:18,960 --> 00:04:22,330
Seo Rin, just play like you used to.

64
00:04:26,540 --> 00:04:27,540
Hurry.

65
00:04:45,060 --> 00:04:48,090
Are you really Oh Jang Mi? Show me.

66
00:04:48,560 --> 00:04:51,400
Show me if you're Ma Seo Rin
or Oh Jang Mi.

67
00:04:51,700 --> 00:04:52,830
Show me who you really are.

68
00:04:55,930 --> 00:04:56,930
What are you doing?

69
00:04:57,540 --> 00:04:59,240
Are you just going to stand there?

70
00:05:27,330 --> 00:05:28,330
That piece...

71
00:05:28,870 --> 00:05:31,400
That's the one Seo Rin
used to play all the time.

72
00:05:32,840 --> 00:05:36,770
It's not something you can play well
without years of practice.

73
00:05:43,250 --> 00:05:46,320
Then there's no doubt that it's Seo Rin.

74
00:06:29,060 --> 00:06:30,260
Ha Neul, I'm so sorry.

75
00:06:31,400 --> 00:06:32,700
Mommy is so sorry.

76
00:06:33,770 --> 00:06:35,670
When you're older and we meet again,

77
00:06:36,800 --> 00:06:38,940
you can resent me all you want.

78
00:06:40,510 --> 00:06:41,940
So for now...

79
00:06:44,910 --> 00:06:45,910
Eat well,

80
00:06:47,480 --> 00:06:48,680
sleep well,

81
00:06:50,650 --> 00:06:51,720
grow up big,

82
00:06:52,320 --> 00:06:53,920
strong and healthy.

83
00:06:56,150 --> 00:06:58,020
My baby, I'm so sorry.

84
00:07:16,210 --> 00:07:19,010
(Please be sure to write down
the child's date of birth.)

85
00:08:16,200 --> 00:08:18,040
Thank goodness, it really is Seo Rin.

86
00:08:18,300 --> 00:08:19,340
Seo Rin.

87
00:08:20,470 --> 00:08:22,040
Even though you've lost your memory,

88
00:08:22,440 --> 00:08:25,140
your skill with the violin
is as amazing as ever.

89
00:08:35,590 --> 00:08:37,820
Seo Rin was a good violinist?

90
00:08:38,360 --> 00:08:39,990
Why is she so good at everything?

91
00:08:39,990 --> 00:08:42,160
This is no time to worry about that.

92
00:08:42,460 --> 00:08:45,060
If you're going to pass as Seo Rin,
you have to be perfect.

93
00:08:45,260 --> 00:08:48,270
CEO Chae could ask you
to play the violin at any moment.

94
00:08:48,570 --> 00:08:52,040
You need to practice just in case.
This piece right here.

95
00:08:52,540 --> 00:08:53,570
Practice this.

96
00:08:53,840 --> 00:08:56,570
What? How am I supposed to do this?

97
00:08:56,570 --> 00:08:58,540
I've never even touched a violin.

98
00:08:58,680 --> 00:09:01,180
And besides,
even if I start practicing now,

99
00:09:01,280 --> 00:09:04,020
how could I possibly match the skills
of someone who's played for years?

100
00:09:04,020 --> 00:09:06,150
CEO Chae will find me out in a heartbeat.

101
00:09:06,220 --> 00:09:09,450
You're so literal.
Who said you had to actually play?

102
00:09:09,690 --> 00:09:10,990
What? Then...

103
00:09:10,990 --> 00:09:14,430
Just fake it. It's like lip-syncing.

104
00:09:15,330 --> 00:09:19,800
So you just want me to learn
how to fake the fingerings?

105
00:09:19,860 --> 00:09:21,130
Exactly.

106
00:09:21,730 --> 00:09:24,370
It's just in case a situation
like that comes up.

107
00:09:24,600 --> 00:09:27,100
I'll play the recording
of Seo Rin's performance.

108
00:09:27,570 --> 00:09:28,810
Here's the speaker.

109
00:09:31,080 --> 00:09:34,750
So all I have to do is
pretend to play, right?

110
00:09:35,880 --> 00:09:38,680
There should be a video
on Seo Rin's phone of her playing.

111
00:09:38,950 --> 00:09:40,180
I'm the one who filmed it for her.

112
00:09:46,360 --> 00:09:47,690
Yes, it's here.

113
00:09:48,430 --> 00:09:50,160
Geum Soon, you're a genius.

114
00:10:48,290 --> 00:10:51,720
Seo Rin, you've loved the violin
ever since you were a little girl.

115
00:10:52,260 --> 00:10:55,760
Your body will remember
even if your mind doesn't.

116
00:10:56,130 --> 00:10:57,430
It's like riding a bike.

117
00:11:18,320 --> 00:11:19,580
That was truly magnificent.

118
00:11:20,180 --> 00:11:21,750
Your performance was truly moving.

119
00:11:23,550 --> 00:11:26,120
It's been a while,
so my hands are a little stiff.

120
00:11:26,420 --> 00:11:28,360
I couldn't quite play at my best.

121
00:11:29,290 --> 00:11:32,330
Looks like General Manager Kang was moved
by our Seo Rin's performance.

122
00:11:32,930 --> 00:11:36,130
I'm telling you, everyone is blown away
when they hear her play.

123
00:11:36,330 --> 00:11:38,940
Yes. I was truly surprised.

124
00:11:44,810 --> 00:11:45,810
Mrs. Yang?

125
00:11:49,810 --> 00:11:52,120
Could you clear this
and bring us some other snacks?

126
00:11:52,750 --> 00:11:53,750
Yes.

127
00:11:59,390 --> 00:12:00,790
What is wrong with you?

128
00:12:02,330 --> 00:12:03,490
I'm so sorry.

129
00:12:06,460 --> 00:12:07,470
Jun Ho!

130
00:12:08,870 --> 00:12:10,170
Oh, my gosh, you're bleeding.

131
00:12:10,570 --> 00:12:11,900
Are you out of your mind?

132
00:12:12,870 --> 00:12:16,040
- Mom!
- Ma'am, I'm fine.

133
00:12:16,070 --> 00:12:17,510
What is wrong with you? He's our guest.

134
00:12:17,710 --> 00:12:18,940
I said I was fine.

135
00:12:19,010 --> 00:12:20,540
What do you mean you're fine?

136
00:12:21,050 --> 00:12:22,510
Get the first-aid kit now!

137
00:12:23,350 --> 00:12:24,920
No, maybe we should go to the hospital.

138
00:12:37,290 --> 00:12:38,530
He's bleeding.

139
00:12:38,800 --> 00:12:40,200
What is going on here?

140
00:12:42,870 --> 00:12:44,140
Father, you're home?

141
00:12:44,940 --> 00:12:47,440
- Good evening, Chairman.
- CEO Chae, what in the world?

142
00:12:47,910 --> 00:12:50,070
What did we just walk in on?

143
00:12:51,010 --> 00:12:52,210
Father, you're home early.

144
00:12:52,480 --> 00:12:55,050
Explain to me what's going on here.

145
00:12:56,510 --> 00:12:59,120
Why in the world is General Manager Kang
in our house,

146
00:12:59,380 --> 00:13:00,850
and what is all this?

147
00:13:01,120 --> 00:13:04,560
Father, I'll explain everything to you
later in private.

148
00:13:05,320 --> 00:13:07,790
Let me give you some first aid.
Please follow me.

149
00:13:14,230 --> 00:13:16,370
Goodness, what is all this?

150
00:13:16,900 --> 00:13:20,140
We come home from a nice evening out
to this mess?

151
00:13:44,660 --> 00:13:46,960
I'm just glad it's not a serious injury.

152
00:13:47,160 --> 00:13:49,970
I never knew you were such a warm
and caring person, Seo Rin.

153
00:13:51,470 --> 00:13:55,440
I want to apologize
for how cold I've been to you.

154
00:13:56,540 --> 00:13:58,040
There's no need to apologize.

155
00:13:59,440 --> 00:14:00,580
I mean it.

156
00:14:00,910 --> 00:14:03,350
People show different sides of themselves
depending on the situation.

157
00:14:03,480 --> 00:14:04,620
Still,

158
00:14:04,920 --> 00:14:08,020
you're just so different
from the Seo Rin I'm used to,

159
00:14:08,650 --> 00:14:10,250
and it's a bit confusing.

160
00:14:10,450 --> 00:14:11,890
And it's making me re-evaluate things.

161
00:14:12,260 --> 00:14:16,830
- Re-evaluating?
- Yes. I've only seen one side of you,

162
00:14:17,360 --> 00:14:19,330
and I judged you completely
on my own terms.

163
00:14:20,100 --> 00:14:22,130
Don't be so quick to put me on a pedestal.

164
00:14:22,530 --> 00:14:25,400
You might be misjudging me again,
for all you know.

165
00:14:30,840 --> 00:14:31,840
So...

166
00:14:32,280 --> 00:14:33,940
you're telling me you invited
General Manager Kang...

167
00:14:33,940 --> 00:14:35,380
without my permission?

168
00:14:35,810 --> 00:14:37,580
Since you were so against it,

169
00:14:37,950 --> 00:14:40,680
I thought I'd bring General Manager Kang
and Seo Rin together first...

170
00:14:41,190 --> 00:14:43,320
so we could have
a more in-depth conversation.

171
00:14:44,690 --> 00:14:47,220
And to encourage them
for all their hard work.

172
00:14:47,290 --> 00:14:48,630
Still, that's no excuse.

173
00:14:49,030 --> 00:14:53,230
You should've asked the Chairman
for permission first.

174
00:14:53,430 --> 00:14:55,430
What do you take the Chairman for,
Hwa Young?

175
00:14:56,330 --> 00:14:58,900
Do you really think
you can just do as you please?

176
00:14:59,500 --> 00:15:00,700
The nerve of you.

177
00:15:00,970 --> 00:15:02,610
And what was all that drama about earlier?

178
00:15:03,510 --> 00:15:04,780
You nearly gave me a heart attack.

179
00:15:07,140 --> 00:15:10,180
In any case,
what Seo Rin wants is important, too.

180
00:15:11,250 --> 00:15:14,180
So we'll consider the marriage issue
in due time.

181
00:15:17,450 --> 00:15:20,520
Yes. How's your hand?

182
00:15:21,160 --> 00:15:24,130
I'm all right.
It's nothing to worry about, Chairman.

183
00:15:24,700 --> 00:15:25,800
It's just a minor injury.

184
00:15:25,900 --> 00:15:28,500
CEO Chae, the more I think about it,
the more I find it ridiculous.

185
00:15:28,830 --> 00:15:30,930
General Manager Kang must've been
so flustered.

186
00:15:31,000 --> 00:15:33,500
You were freaking out more than he was.

187
00:15:33,640 --> 00:15:35,270
When Seo Rin would get hurt as a child,

188
00:15:35,640 --> 00:15:38,210
that old habit of mine
just suddenly kicked in.

189
00:15:38,480 --> 00:15:39,610
General Manager Kang, I'm sorry.

190
00:15:40,080 --> 00:15:41,450
You must have been taken aback.

191
00:15:41,710 --> 00:15:43,450
Not at all. It's fine.

192
00:15:43,850 --> 00:15:46,550
My own mother has never done that for me.

193
00:15:48,790 --> 00:15:49,920
I should be going now.

194
00:15:50,020 --> 00:15:53,960
All right. Seo Rin,
why don't you see him out?

195
00:15:54,120 --> 00:15:55,190
Yes, Grandfather.

196
00:15:55,530 --> 00:15:56,690
General Manager Kang.

197
00:16:20,680 --> 00:16:23,690
Thank you for inviting me to dinner today.

198
00:16:24,990 --> 00:16:26,490
My mom was the one who invited you.

199
00:16:27,060 --> 00:16:30,330
But I'm afraid we were very rude
to you today.

200
00:16:30,530 --> 00:16:34,930
Hearing you play the violin
more than made up for it.

201
00:16:36,000 --> 00:16:37,600
I was truly moved by it.

202
00:16:38,300 --> 00:16:40,500
Would you play for me again sometime?

203
00:16:41,540 --> 00:16:42,540
That's...

204
00:16:43,170 --> 00:16:45,140
not something you get to hear
just any time.

205
00:16:45,580 --> 00:16:47,010
In fact, you might never hear it again.

206
00:16:47,440 --> 00:16:48,450
What?

207
00:16:49,580 --> 00:16:50,610
Anyway...

208
00:16:51,050 --> 00:16:54,790
My mom was really out of character today.
Please don't mind her.

209
00:16:54,850 --> 00:16:59,320
I took it as her sizing me up
as a potential son-in-law.

210
00:16:59,590 --> 00:17:00,660
A potential son-in-law?

211
00:17:01,160 --> 00:17:02,190
That's ridiculous.

212
00:17:02,490 --> 00:17:04,400
It's not like anyone said
I was going to marry you.

213
00:17:06,300 --> 00:17:10,970
So, you're saying that after the accident,
you're just not that into me anymore?

214
00:17:11,100 --> 00:17:13,200
Weren't you the one
who called me a stalker?

215
00:17:14,840 --> 00:17:16,270
Let's just say I've changed my mind.

216
00:17:16,940 --> 00:17:17,940
Don't tell me...

217
00:17:18,610 --> 00:17:20,480
Are you actually serious
about marrying me?

218
00:17:21,210 --> 00:17:22,210
You're not, are you?

219
00:17:22,350 --> 00:17:24,850
Are you saying you don't want
to marry me anymore?

220
00:17:25,880 --> 00:17:27,990
I'm not used to this version of you.

221
00:17:28,490 --> 00:17:29,490
Tell me about it.

222
00:17:29,850 --> 00:17:32,160
I never imagined
a day like this would come.

223
00:17:32,860 --> 00:17:36,230
You were always my idol,
someone I admired from afar.

224
00:17:36,530 --> 00:17:37,530
So then...

225
00:17:37,800 --> 00:17:41,470
you do remember that
you used to like me, right?

226
00:17:54,710 --> 00:17:55,710
What?

227
00:17:56,810 --> 00:17:57,850
That car...

228
00:17:58,820 --> 00:18:00,180
What's Baek Ho doing here?

229
00:18:01,990 --> 00:18:02,990
Jun Ho.

230
00:18:06,320 --> 00:18:07,890
Hello, Lawyer Kang.

231
00:18:08,430 --> 00:18:11,730
How did you end up
coming here with Hong Ju?

232
00:18:12,030 --> 00:18:14,200
I was invited over
to Baek Ho's place today.

233
00:18:14,800 --> 00:18:16,330
We're just coming from his place now.

234
00:18:17,570 --> 00:18:18,570
Invited?

235
00:18:19,070 --> 00:18:20,240
It's not like that.

236
00:18:20,770 --> 00:18:24,480
My mom and Hong Ju just had dinner,
and she dropped by for a moment.

237
00:18:25,780 --> 00:18:27,280
I see.

238
00:18:32,050 --> 00:18:33,250
How was dinner, Jun Ho?

239
00:18:33,450 --> 00:18:34,490
Did you have fun?

240
00:18:34,750 --> 00:18:38,790
Yes. I was really moved
by Seo Rin's violin performance.

241
00:18:40,390 --> 00:18:41,730
Really?

242
00:18:44,800 --> 00:18:46,760
Hong Ju, you should get going now.

243
00:18:46,760 --> 00:18:48,770
Hey, Baek Ho, perfect timing.

244
00:18:49,370 --> 00:18:50,570
We can go home together.

245
00:18:52,300 --> 00:18:54,970
Seo Rin. I had a wonderful time today.

246
00:19:03,550 --> 00:19:04,550
Good night.

247
00:19:11,260 --> 00:19:12,260
Good night, everyone.

248
00:19:17,190 --> 00:19:18,630
I had a great time today, Baek Ho.

249
00:19:27,700 --> 00:19:28,870
Hey, what's the hold-up?

250
00:19:29,270 --> 00:19:30,340
Let's go.

251
00:19:35,950 --> 00:19:36,950
What's his deal?

252
00:19:37,380 --> 00:19:38,420
Hurry up, it's cold.

253
00:19:40,620 --> 00:19:41,620
Oh, Jun Ho.

254
00:19:43,250 --> 00:19:45,220
My poor boy. My heart aches for you.

255
00:19:47,690 --> 00:19:51,190
I tried to make you one meal,
and all I did was hurt your hand.

256
00:19:52,230 --> 00:19:53,760
And I just made a fool of myself.

257
00:19:58,140 --> 00:20:01,310
All I did was embarrass myself
in front of my boy.

258
00:20:17,550 --> 00:20:20,320
Jang Mi, we didn't get a chance
to talk earlier with Hong Ju there.

259
00:20:20,520 --> 00:20:24,560
Actually, I was upset
when I saw you with Hong Ju.

260
00:20:24,860 --> 00:20:25,860
You were?

261
00:20:26,460 --> 00:20:27,630
I'm glad to hear that.

262
00:20:27,630 --> 00:20:30,200
What? What do you mean you're glad?

263
00:20:30,300 --> 00:20:32,200
You're jealous right now, aren't you?

264
00:20:32,740 --> 00:20:34,640
Which means you like me.

265
00:20:34,640 --> 00:20:36,370
- Am I wrong?
- You're wrong.

266
00:20:36,870 --> 00:20:38,180
I'm annoyed.

267
00:20:38,610 --> 00:20:41,950
If you get chummy with Hong Ju again,
I'm done with you. Got it?

268
00:20:42,180 --> 00:20:43,650
Nope, I don't think I do.

269
00:20:44,180 --> 00:20:46,280
As if you won't be all chummy
with my brother.

270
00:20:46,350 --> 00:20:47,620
You're being so petty.

271
00:20:48,050 --> 00:20:50,750
- You really can't tell how I feel?
- No, I have no idea.

272
00:20:51,720 --> 00:20:55,790
The way my brother looks at you
makes me nervous.

273
00:20:56,190 --> 00:20:57,190
What?

274
00:20:57,190 --> 00:20:58,860
My brother has never once
looked at anyone else...

275
00:20:58,860 --> 00:21:01,430
so tenderly like this before.

276
00:21:01,700 --> 00:21:04,470
But the way he looked at you
was so full of tenderness.

277
00:21:05,170 --> 00:21:08,340
So just tell me already that you love me.

278
00:21:09,640 --> 00:21:10,910
Don't be anxious.

279
00:21:13,440 --> 00:21:14,780
I love you, Baek Ho.

280
00:21:16,580 --> 00:21:19,580
I will love you too
until the end of the world...

281
00:21:19,950 --> 00:21:23,790
No, even after that.
I'll love you forever and ever.

282
00:21:24,190 --> 00:21:26,990
- Promise you'll never change.
- Promise you won't either.

283
00:21:39,370 --> 00:21:40,400
Hong Ju.

284
00:21:40,540 --> 00:21:42,610
Don't leave on an empty stomach.
Drink this before you go.

285
00:21:42,670 --> 00:21:43,670
I'm late.

286
00:21:46,910 --> 00:21:49,150
I still can't get over how strange it is.

287
00:21:50,150 --> 00:21:53,450
- What is?
- Chae Hwa Young was like this...

288
00:21:55,250 --> 00:21:57,450
- to General Manager Kang.
- What?

289
00:21:58,090 --> 00:21:59,720
- Seriously?
- She claimed it was just...

290
00:21:59,720 --> 00:22:02,530
an old habit from
when she was raising Seo Rin.

291
00:22:02,630 --> 00:22:03,760
But isn't that ridiculous?

292
00:22:04,130 --> 00:22:05,930
I mean, he was like an enemy to her,

293
00:22:05,930 --> 00:22:08,170
but now she's trying to make him
her son-in-law?

294
00:22:09,270 --> 00:22:11,940
I can't believe she invited him over
while the Chairman was away.

295
00:22:12,270 --> 00:22:15,010
You're right.
CEO Chae has been acting strangely lately.

296
00:22:15,810 --> 00:22:18,840
You don't think Chae Hwa Young
has a thing for Kang Jun Ho, do you?

297
00:22:18,840 --> 00:22:19,880
What?

298
00:22:20,380 --> 00:22:22,510
Mom, be serious.

299
00:22:22,710 --> 00:22:24,180
He's young enough to be her son.

300
00:22:24,250 --> 00:22:27,920
Anyway, I also heard
she's being blackmailed lately.

301
00:22:28,090 --> 00:22:31,020
There's a lot of suspicious stuff
going on with that woman.

302
00:22:31,520 --> 00:22:35,090
So when you're at the office,
keep a close eye on her for me.

303
00:22:35,390 --> 00:22:38,960
Our number one priority is
taking that woman down.

304
00:22:42,670 --> 00:22:44,970
What? Oh Jang Mi's hospital room?

305
00:22:45,340 --> 00:22:49,140
Yes. According to the nurse,
her guardian requested no visitors.

306
00:22:49,770 --> 00:22:52,840
What's that supposed to mean?
Are they trying to keep her under wraps?

307
00:22:53,010 --> 00:22:55,110
But I thought you confirmed
she was Seo Rin yesterday.

308
00:22:55,850 --> 00:22:57,880
So why do you keep worrying about her?

309
00:22:58,720 --> 00:23:00,450
I don't know why,
but something keeps bothering me.

310
00:23:02,420 --> 00:23:05,190
You are keeping a close eye on
Suk Hee's Side Dishes, right?

311
00:23:05,590 --> 00:23:07,120
Suk Hee's Side Dishes?

312
00:23:07,820 --> 00:23:08,860
Yes.

313
00:23:09,060 --> 00:23:10,730
Keep a close eye on Oh Tae Pyung too.

314
00:23:11,060 --> 00:23:12,460
Something's off about him.

315
00:23:14,700 --> 00:23:16,800
What? Suk Hee's Side Dishes?

316
00:23:17,830 --> 00:23:18,840
Where is that?

317
00:23:18,900 --> 00:23:21,710
Come on, it's that place I bought
side dishes from last time.

318
00:23:21,710 --> 00:23:23,240
You loved them too.

319
00:23:23,810 --> 00:23:27,810
- That place?
- I think the blackmailer is Oh Tae Pyung.

320
00:23:28,510 --> 00:23:30,480
She said to keep a close eye on
Oh Tae Pyung.

321
00:23:30,710 --> 00:23:35,190
So the guy blackmailing Chae Hwa Young
is at Suk Hee's Side Dishes?

322
00:23:35,250 --> 00:23:36,890
Yes, I heard it with my own two ears.

323
00:23:37,190 --> 00:23:38,790
That she said something
wasn't right about Oh Tae Pyung.

324
00:23:39,160 --> 00:23:40,160
Really?

325
00:23:42,460 --> 00:23:46,230
Okay. I'll go check it out myself,
and then we'll know for sure.

326
00:23:46,700 --> 00:23:47,700
Okay, got to go. Bye.

327
00:23:48,370 --> 00:23:51,500
(Suk Hee's Side Dishes)

328
00:23:54,170 --> 00:23:55,170
I'm heading out.

329
00:23:56,910 --> 00:23:59,580
Hey, Oh Tae Pyung.
Why are you dressed like that?

330
00:24:00,140 --> 00:24:01,380
What do you mean? They're clothes.

331
00:24:01,380 --> 00:24:03,310
Why are you carrying a helmet?

332
00:24:03,710 --> 00:24:06,620
Tae Pyung looks so handsome.
Tae Pyung is dashing.

333
00:24:07,150 --> 00:24:10,220
Mom, please. He doesn't have
a penny to his name,

334
00:24:10,290 --> 00:24:12,690
but he walks around acting
like he's some big shot.

335
00:24:12,760 --> 00:24:14,190
Think whatever you want.

336
00:24:14,660 --> 00:24:15,860
I'm heading out for a delivery.

337
00:24:15,930 --> 00:24:17,760
Mom, I'm off. See you later.

338
00:24:17,760 --> 00:24:18,860
Oh my!

339
00:24:21,260 --> 00:24:22,300
I'm sorry.

340
00:24:33,340 --> 00:24:35,050
What is that intoxicating scent?

341
00:24:35,280 --> 00:24:38,480
Oh my, I think I'm hearing bells
ringing in my chest.

342
00:24:40,450 --> 00:24:41,890
I'm so sorry, ma'am.

343
00:24:42,020 --> 00:24:43,090
Please, come on in.

344
00:24:48,690 --> 00:24:51,360
I had no idea
such a handsome man worked here.

345
00:24:52,460 --> 00:24:54,500
It's been ages since my heart
has pounded like this.

346
00:25:04,040 --> 00:25:05,110
(Jang Mi's father, Dream Hotel,
Father, Chae Hwa Young)

347
00:25:05,110 --> 00:25:08,380
When Jang Mi's father
figured everything out,

348
00:25:08,950 --> 00:25:11,350
he and Chae Hwa Young got into a struggle
in Dream Hotel's underground garage,

349
00:25:11,880 --> 00:25:14,480
and he ended up getting hurt.

350
00:25:20,060 --> 00:25:23,290
(Crime scene)

351
00:25:24,260 --> 00:25:26,130
Then, to cover up her crime,

352
00:25:26,660 --> 00:25:28,330
she took his unconscious body...

353
00:25:28,730 --> 00:25:30,970
and just left him on the road
at the accident site.

354
00:25:36,870 --> 00:25:38,380
(Father)

355
00:25:38,440 --> 00:25:39,640
But as fate would have it,

356
00:25:39,940 --> 00:25:41,810
my dad was heading to the Dream Resort...

357
00:25:41,810 --> 00:25:43,410
- because of an issue,
- Oh, no...

358
00:25:43,510 --> 00:25:45,620
and he ended up hitting
Jang Mi's father with his car.

359
00:26:00,130 --> 00:26:02,700
Gosh, look at my handsome husband.

360
00:26:03,400 --> 00:26:05,440
If you go to the Dream Hotel
looking that handsome,

361
00:26:05,740 --> 00:26:08,170
what will I do if CEO Chae
falls head over heels for you?

362
00:26:08,670 --> 00:26:10,540
You and your wild imagination.

363
00:26:10,970 --> 00:26:14,210
That'll never happen in a million years,
so don't worry.

364
00:26:14,280 --> 00:26:16,110
Really?

365
00:26:16,110 --> 00:26:18,080
Mom, don't you worry about a thing.

366
00:26:18,380 --> 00:26:21,950
Plus, I'm working at the Dream Hotel now,
so I'll definitely keep an eye on Dad.

367
00:26:22,120 --> 00:26:23,550
- What?
- That's a great idea.

368
00:26:23,620 --> 00:26:27,860
Your father is continuing his consulting
for the industry-academia partnership.

369
00:26:28,020 --> 00:26:31,330
He'll be in and out
of the Dream Hotel for a while,

370
00:26:31,390 --> 00:26:33,230
so, Baek Ho, you need to keep
a close eye on your dad.

371
00:26:33,300 --> 00:26:35,800
Stop joking in front of him.

372
00:26:35,800 --> 00:26:37,970
- Dad, shall we go?
- Yes, let's go.

373
00:26:38,600 --> 00:26:40,470
- We're off.
- Bye.

374
00:26:49,010 --> 00:26:50,980
I'm so sorry you had to witness
something like that...

375
00:26:51,750 --> 00:26:53,320
after inviting you over.

376
00:26:53,680 --> 00:26:54,780
It's quite all right.

377
00:26:55,820 --> 00:26:57,790
Seo Rin's performance was so moving...

378
00:26:58,390 --> 00:27:00,620
that your little mistake
doesn't bother me in the slightest.

379
00:27:02,690 --> 00:27:05,560
I have another engagement,
so I'll be taking my leave now.

380
00:27:15,470 --> 00:27:16,510
What have I done?

381
00:27:17,210 --> 00:27:19,340
This relationship I've worked
so hard to build...

382
00:27:20,140 --> 00:27:21,810
is ruined over something so pointless.

383
00:27:28,950 --> 00:27:29,950
General Manager Kang...

384
00:28:14,300 --> 00:28:15,770
(The First Man)

385
00:28:15,830 --> 00:28:17,730
A video of me on a power trip?
That's absurd.

386
00:28:17,970 --> 00:28:21,670
What on earth have you been up to?

387
00:28:22,040 --> 00:28:23,940
So the person you had to meet was Baek Ho?

388
00:28:24,270 --> 00:28:25,440
Baek Ho, that punk...

389
00:28:25,780 --> 00:28:27,710
Is there really something
going on between you two?

390
00:28:28,310 --> 00:28:31,650
You're the one who called my father
to the scene of the accident, weren't you?

391
00:28:31,850 --> 00:28:33,120
You'd better be careful.

392
00:28:33,120 --> 00:28:36,620
I will prove you framed my father
and take you down.

393
00:28:40,720 --> 00:28:42,730
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
